        "id": "1",
        "body": '<p><span style="font-size:22pt"><span style="font-family:Arial"><span style="color:#000000"><strong>Selection UX</strong></span></span></span></p><p><span style="font-size:16pt"><span style="font-family:Arial"><span style="color:#000000">Creating selection always depends on how many items/options it contains. For fewer items, we can just display them as:</span></span></span></p><p><img alt="" src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dqrtlfjc0/image/upload/v1676637236/Oneguru%20Projects/Selection%20UX/4_aoj475.png" style="width:60%"/></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-size:16pt"><span style="font-family:Arial"><span style="color:#000000">However, this design wouldn&rsquo;t be feasible if we have multiple options to display.</span></span></span></p><p><img alt="" src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dqrtlfjc0/image/upload/v1676637236/Oneguru%20Projects/Selection%20UX/1_wcspow.png" style="width:60%"/></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-size:16pt"><span style="font-family:Arial"><span style="color:#000000">And radio selections would just aggravate the problem</span></span></span></p><p><img alt="" src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dqrtlfjc0/image/upload/v1676637236/Oneguru%20Projects/Selection%20UX/2_cjrhya.png" style="width:60%"/></p><p><br/>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-size:16pt"><span style="font-family:Arial"><span style="color:#000000">As much as possible, refrain from displaying selections for several options that take up a lot of space on the page. We can do it by showing the options upon clicking a select dropdown.</span></span></span></p><p><img alt="" src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dqrtlfjc0/image/upload/v1676637235/Oneguru%20Projects/Selection%20UX/3_ilus7p.png" style="width:60%"/></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>',
